é represents the [[Guinea national football team]] internationally.
==Career== ===Fulham=== Fulham tried to sign Cissé from Belgium side [[Standard Liège]] in January 2017 but it wasn't until 7 July 2017 that Fulham finally signed him for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11681/10720468/fulham-hold-talks-with-standard-liege-to-sign-ibrahima-cisse |title=Fulham hold talks with Standard Liege to sign Ibrahima Cisse |publisher=Sky Sports |author=Lyall Thomas |date=7 January 2017 |accessdate=8 July 2017 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2017/july/07/cisse-signs |title=Cisse Signs |publisher=Fulham Football Club |date= 7 July 2017 |accessdate=8 July 2017 }}</ref>
==International career== Cissé was born in Belgium and is of Guinean descent. He was formerly a youth international for Belgium. However, he pledged his international allegiance to Guinea in March 2018.<ref>https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/43590375</ref>
On 25 April 2018, Cissé accepted an invitation to represent the [[Guinea national football team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.afrik-foot.com/guinee-apres-seka-3-nouveaux-binationaux-disent-oui|title=Guinée : après Seka, 3 nouveaux binationaux disent oui - Afrik-foot.com : l'actualité du football africain|website=www.afrik-foot.com}}</ref> He made his professional debut for Guinea in a 1-0 [[2019 Africa Cup of Nations qualification]] win over [[Central African Republic national football team|Central African Republic]] on 9 September 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cafonline.com/en-us/competitions/32ndeditionoftotalafricacupofnations/MatchDetails?MatchId=owNhdRjYIdDzTEAyxtDiW2kQIwXjM8B3NHZ1Lek2qNhXOgH6h16nzfF4DCuKHVOd|title=Guinea - Central African Republic 09/09/2018|website=www.cafonline.com}}</ref>
